The paper deals with constraint satisfaction problems (CSPs) over infinite domains, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The use of algebraic structures and identities to study CSPs suggests that the paper belongs to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of polymorphism clones, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The proposed strategy for reducing the infinite domain CSP dichotomy conjecture to the finite case involves computational complexity theory, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the Computational Complexity (cs.CC) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper characterizes a topological property of $\omega$-categorical core structures, which suggests that it may also belong to the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
